{"id":13987,"name":null,"username":"Lawrence","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/lawrence/{size}/607_2.png","created_at":"2012-02-19T19:27:12.000Z","cooked":"<p>Ive always wanted to do something like that with editing tools, but Im no programmer and Im not sure its even possible at the moment<br>\nSome sort of hard mode for LBA2, which would basically mean less clover boxes to be found, a lot more roaming enemies, more health for all enemies, that sort of thing. My guess is that most of this could be accomplished by scene editing, and even someone like uhm me, could erase a few clover boxes and increase enemy health, the real problem would be adding more enemies, I have literally no clue about how actor AI works. I tried to figure out stuff by reading pre-existing enemy scripts, making small changes to them, trial and error and all that but I just dont get it.</p>\n<p>Why LBA2? Well, because it needs a hard mode more badly than LBA1 <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/stuck_out_tongue.png?v=12\" title=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> that game is a hard mode in itself, thanks to unforgiving recovery time from enemy attacks, insane firing rates and no way to quickly get out of the way.</p>\n<p>Im conscious that a lot is still unknown about LBA2 file formats, but I cant help but think this can be done as it doesnt require heavy modifications.</p>\n<p>Go ahead, crush my dreams <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/smiley.png?v=12\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":smiley:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T15:27:10.553Z","reply_count":9,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":65.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":13984,"topic_slug":"lba2-hard-mode-concept","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"raw":"I've always wanted to do something like that with editing tools, but I'm no programmer and I'm not sure it's even possible at the moment...\nSome sort of \"hard mode\" for LBA2, which would basically mean less clover boxes to be found, a lot more roaming enemies, more health for all enemies, that sort of thing. My guess is that most of this could be accomplished by scene editing, and even someone like... uhm... me, could erase a few clover boxes and increase enemy health, the real problem would be adding more enemies, I have literally no clue about how actor AI works. I tried to figure out stuff by reading pre-existing enemy scripts, making small changes to them, trial and error and all that but I just don't get it.\n\nWhy LBA2? Well, because it needs a hard mode more badly than LBA1 :p that game is a hard mode in itself, thanks to unforgiving recovery time from enemy attacks, insane firing rates and no way to quickly get out of the way.\n\nI'm conscious that a lot is still unknown about LBA2 file formats, but I can't help but think this can be done as it doesn't require heavy modifications.\n\nGo ahead, crush my dreams :D","actions_summary":[{"id":2,"can_act":true},{"id":6,"can_act":true},{"id":3,"can_act":true},{"id":4,"can_act":true},{"id":8,"can_act":true},{"id":10,"can_act":true},{"id":7,"can_act":true}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":3071,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/lba2-hard-mode-concept/13984/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false}
{"id":372578,"name":null,"username":"Zink","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/zink/{size}/61_2.png","created_at":"2012-02-19T20:53:13.000Z","cooked":"<p>We have no tool to easily edit LBA 2 scenes. LBArchitect is aiming that in one of future versions, but it is a very distant future (it may never happen as well).</p>\n<p>Sorry to break your dreams <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2024-10-25T18:52:11.840Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":1,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":0,"readers_count":0,"score":0.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":13984,"topic_slug":"lba2-hard-mode-concept","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":3071,"username":"Lawrence","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/lawrence/{size}/607_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"raw":"We have no tool to easily edit LBA 2 scenes. LBArchitect is aiming that in one of future versions, but it is a very distant future (it may never happen as well).\n\nSorry to break your dreams :)","actions_summary":[{"id":2,"can_act":true},{"id":6,"can_act":true},{"id":3,"can_act":true},{"id":4,"can_act":true},{"id":8,"can_act":true},{"id":10,"can_act":true},{"id":7,"can_act":true}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":184,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/lba2-hard-mode-concept/13984/2","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":nu